OL,6,FChief Executive Officer of Gamble
OL,7,FAware, Zoe Osmond says that "Blurring
OL,8,Fof lines between gambling and gaming
OL,9,Fare confusing, and children are
OL,10,Ftherefore not aware of the risks, and
OL,11,Fwe know that a lot of the content out
OL,12,Fthere is geared to be bright, loud,
OL,13,Fcatchy, cartoon-like, and that
OL,14,Fattracts children and that takes them
OL,15,Fdown the there.
OL,17,F"So there needs to be much stricter
OL,18,Fregulation around the type of content
OL,19,Fthat is also allowed to run."
